    <name>
      <text>PT.8.9 (Infinite sum 1)</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Let \( u_1, u_2, \ldots, u_n, \ldots \) be an arithmetic sequence and \( v_1, v_2, \ldots, v_n, \ldots \) be a geometric sequence. The first terms \( u_1\) and \( v_1\) are both equal to {@t1@}, and the third terms \( u_3\) and \( v_3\) are both equal to {@t3@}.</p><p><b>(a)</b> Find \(u_{@n@} = \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]</p><p><b>(b)</b> Given that \( v_1, v_2, \ldots \) is a sequence of positive numbers, calculate \( \displaystyle \sum_{n=1}^{\infty}v_n .\)</p><p>\( \displaystyle \sum_{n=1}^{\infty}v_n = \) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p><b>(a)</b> For the arithmetic sequence we have: \[ \begin{align*} u_n &amp;=u_1+(n-1)d&nbsp; \\ &amp;= {@t1+('n-1)*'d@}.\end{align*} \] Since \(u_3={@t3@}\), this gives \[ \begin{align*} {@t1+(3-1)*'d@} &amp;= {@t3@} \\ 2d&amp;= {@t3@}-{@t1@}&nbsp; \\ d&amp;= {@d@}.\end{align*} \] Hence \( u_{@n@} = {@t1@}+({@n@}-1)({@d@}) = {@ta1@}\).</p><p><b>(b)</b> For the geometric sequence we have \[ v_n= v_1 r^{n-1} \] So \[ {@t3@} = {@t1@} r^2 \] \[ r= {@r@} \] Hence \[ S = \frac{@t1@}{1-{@r@}}= {@ta2@} \]</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
